        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer16014723" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14290092062445644981">I really liked this book, and have therefore come to the conclusion that books written for children can be higher quality writing than books written for adults because there isn&apos;t this pressure to impress with heavy metaphor and poignant statements about life. When adults write for adults there is too much pressure, adults writing for children understand that it is the story and the characters that matter most, and if those two are well written then I think you have a deep, satisfying book. </span>
  <span id="freeText14290092062445644981" style="display:none">I really liked this book, and have therefore come to the conclusion that books written for children can be higher quality writing than books written for adults because there isn't this pressure to impress with heavy metaphor and poignant statements about life. When adults write for adults there is too much pressure, adults writing for children understand that it is the story and the characters that matter most, and if those two are well written then I think you have a deep, satisfying book. </span>
