<div id="review_3112270488" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3112270488" />
    <a title="Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty"><img alt="Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1304653755p2/796425.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3112270488?book_show_action=true">Dec 31, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)" href="/user/show/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty">Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780395071144" href="/book/show/1076924.The_Witch_of_Blackbird_Pond">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty?shelf=all-fiction">all-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty?shelf=books-little-me-loved">books-little-me-loved</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3112270488" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17603619219350693778">My last book of 2019. (So I lied a few hours ago about the other book I thought would be my last. But this one really is, I promise.)<br/><br/>I recently recommended this book to a Good Reads friend because I had fond memories of it from childhood. Re-reading it now as an adult reminded me once again that I was a much more patient reader as a youngster than I am now. The book is well-researched and finely written, but it doesn&apos;t really get interesting until 40% of the way through when Kit finally meets Ha</span>
  <span id="freeText17603619219350693778" style="display:none">My last book of 2019. (So I lied a few hours ago about the other book I thought would be my last. But this one really is, I promise.)<br /><br />I recently recommended this book to a Good Reads friend because I had fond memories of it from childhood. Re-reading it now as an adult reminded me once again that I was a much more patient reader as a youngster than I am now. The book is well-researched and finely written, but it doesn't really get interesting until 40% of the way through when Kit finally meets Hannah. <br /><br />I realize now that my warm fuzzy memories of the book were only the parts where Kit hangs out in Hannah's cottage on Blackbird Pond. I had completely forgotten all the nasty barbaric Puritan stuff like putting people in the stockade for punishment and the surgeon feeding Judith ground roasted toads to try to cure her illness. And of course, as a girl I think I was mostly oblivious to all the drama over snagging a husband. I doubt it made any impression on me at all. Looking at it now, it seems like a good candidate for "my first historical romance". There really is quite a lot of he loves me/he loves me not angsty stuff filling up the pages.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17603619219350693778" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


